~A bulging disc, a brutal ache,
A weight that no one else can take,
A pain that makes it hard to stand,
Like fire spreading through the land.

It starts so small, a dull, faint throb,
But soon it grows into a job
Pinning down each movement made,
Until we're trapped, afraid.

The bulging disc, a thorn that pricks,
A cruel reminder that life is mixed
With twists and turns, and up and downs,
That make us scream and wear us down.

Yet deep within this pain and woe,
There's growth and healing, don't you know?
For every bulging disc reveals
A strength we never knew we wield.

So let the pain flow through your soul,
And know that you can still be whole.
Take comfort in the strength you've gained,
From every hardship, every pain.

That's a wrap on Circus of Strength 2.  This comp is typically our more stressful comp to run. It's five strongman events and circus acts between each event. This event is special, because it's one of a kind. No where in the US can you compete in a real circus tent with all the accoutrements. Mc Clown, lions, tigers, Wheel of death, unicycle performance and acrobatic performances really set the tone. 

But why do it if it's sooo stressful? We want promote strength sports and give athletes the show they didn't know they needed. Strongman has deep roots in the circus community and I feel like we really hit the hammer on the head with this event.

I really want to thank everyone that made this event happen. All our crew at @swbarbell_fitness @_mrmeathead_ for welding skills, @cmcircus , @bearfootshoes @sambelliveauu @max.boudreault23 @joewdoerr @lawtonfoodbank @brewhousebarbell
